messageBody:
> should have known you'd have one ;)

That's the goal of JUnit-addons: providing functionalities not present in the
standard JUnit. So if you're looking for something (not too exotic) chances are
that JUnit-addons has just what you want.

I just made a release this week-end and it should please all the users
complaining about "expected <......> but was <...,...>".
